quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  19,96,"Surely, those who believe and do the righteous deeds, for them the Rahman (All-Merciful) will create love."
  19,97,"So We have made it easy through your tongue so that you give with it the good news to the God-fearing and warn with it an obstinate people."
  19,98,"And how many a generation We have destroyed before them. Do you sense (the presence of) any one of them or hear from them even a whisper?"
  20,1,"Ta-Ha [ 1]"
  20,2,"We did not reveal the Qur'an to you to (make you) face hardship"
  20,3,"rather to remind him who has the fear"
  20,4,"a revelation from the One Who created the earth, and the heavens so high."
  20,5,"The Rahman (the All-Merciful) has positioned Himself on the Throne."
  20,6,"To Him belongs whatever there is in the heavens, whatever there is in the earth, whatever there is between them and whatever there is beneath the soil."
  20,7,"And if you pronounce the word aloud, then (it makes no difference, for) He certainly knows the secret and what is even more hidden."
  20,8,"(Such is) Allah. There is no god but He. For Him are the Beautiful Names."
  20,9,"And has there come to you the story of Musa?"
  20,10,"When he saw a fire and said to his family, "Wait. I have noticed a fire. Perhaps I bring you an ember from it, or find some guidance by the fire.""
  20,11,"So when he came to it, he was called, "0 Musa,"
  20,12,"it is Me, your Lord, so remove your shoes; you are in the sacred valley of Tuwa."